Class Element

  • java.lang.Object
    • afterSOLIDrevisionEHL.model.Element
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Requestable, java.lang.Comparable<Element>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    ComposedElement, SimpleElement

    public abstract class Element
extends java.lang.Object
implements Requestable, java.lang.Comparable<Element>
    Class whose instances represent elements that can be put in a shelf. Elements have a title, they may or may not be in a shelf, they occupy a certain number of units of space and they have an availability status.
    Author:
    (original) Daniel Gomes, Filipe Maia, Pedro Antunes, (revisionSOLID) Eva Gomes, Hugo Leal, Lucas Andrade

        public int compareTo(Element element)
        Sorts instances of Element by lexicological order of the field title (using the method compareTo of class String); if two instances have the same title , they will be sorted by lexicological order of the String representation of their classes (obtained using the methods getClass of class Object, toString of class Class and compareTo of class String).
        Specified by:
        compareTo in interface java.lang.Comparable<Element>
        Parameters:
        element - The instance of Element with which to compare to.
        Returns:
        A value less than 0 if this is less than element; 0 if this and element have the same title and the same runtime type or a value greater than 0 if this is greater than element.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - If element is null.

        public boolean isInstanceWithTheSameTypeAndTitleAs(java.lang.Object other)
        Compares the type and the title of this and other.

        This method produces the same result as the method equals of class Element yet its existence ensures the comparison of two instances of Element by looking only at their type and title while; if using the method equals of class Element it might be overriden and the comparison criteria could be different.

        Parameters:
        other - The instance whose type and title are to be compared with.
        Returns:
        true if this and other are two instances with the same type and title;
        false otherwise.
